      | > Where do we want to be?
      |    > Metrics:
               > specific
               > measurable
               > achievable
               > relevant
               > Time bound
     `|  > How do we get there? 
               > Service Improvement Plans
               > Process improvement Plans
          [ Determine various activities and processes can be improved upon to add value that stakeholders are expecting.
      |  > Take Action:
          > Execution of Improvements.
      | > Did we get there?
      | > How do we maintain momentum?
           - Market / Reinforce.
      
      | > Warranty: Defined as a the assurance that a product or service will meet agreed requirements.
      |   > When a service is referred to as "fit for use". 
      |   > Warranty is usually concerned with availability, capacity, capability, and security requirements.
       
[ Four Dimensions of Service Management ]
- Organizations & People  > vary in size, complexity, legal structure 
- Information & Technology
- Partners & Suppliers
- Value Streams & Processes
      > Specific combinations of SVC activities coupled with various practices to accomplish an objective.
          > Provides steps that are needed to successfully deliver a service to a consumer.
          > Each value stream wil be designed to accomplish a specific goal, task, objective.


