[ ITIL Practices (Foundation Level) ]
- General Management (Change, Incident, Problem)
          > Change Enablement
               > The need to make beneficial changes
               > The need to protect customers and users from the adverse effect of changes.

- Service Management (Service Desk, Request Mgmt)


 > Monitoring and Event Management Practice
               > Goal: Practice of systematically observing services and service components and recording and reporting selected changes of state identified as events.
               > Helps to identify and respond to current or potential problems or incidents
                    (reactively or proactively)
               > Event: Any changes of state that has significance for the management of a service or other configuration item.
               > Recognized through notifications created by the service,  configuration items or monitoring tool

- Technical Management (Deployment, Monitoring)


- Incident Management
          > The practice of minimizing the negative impact of incidents by restoring normal service operations as quickly as possible.
               > Goal: Restore normal service as quickly as possible and minimize business impact.
                    > Key Roles: Creating incidents records, diagnostics and resolving incidents.
                         > escalating incidents to support teams for resolution.

